{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"A plugin whose manifest is missing a required field is rejected before any code from that plugin is executed.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real failure risk is in loader wiring: manifest read/validation must gate module import. A unit test of only the validator can pass while loader still imports plugin code too early.","test_description":"Create a temp plugin directory with one plugin containing an invalid `manifest.json` (e.g., missing `name`) and an entry module that writes a sentinel file or mutates a shared log at top-level import time. Run the real loader against the directory. Assert: loader reports manifest validation failure, plugin is not loaded, and sentinel side effect never occurs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.8,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When plugin A declares a dependency on plugin B, plugin B's `onLoad` hook is called before plugin A's.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is dependency resolution + hook orchestration across multiple plugin modules. Mocking one layer can hide ordering bugs in actual loader sequencing.","test_description":"Create two real plugin folders: `B` with no deps and `A` with `dependencies:[\"B\"]`. Each `onLoad` appends its name to a shared in-memory/event log. Execute loader over the directory. Assert hook call order is `[\"B\",\"A\"]`.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.84,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"When two plugins each declare a dependency on the other, the loader reports the cycle and loads neither.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Cycle bugs often emerge when graph detection is integrated with loader state transitions (reporting + suppressing loads). A pure graph unit test may miss that loader still imports or initializes plugins.","test_description":"Create plugins `A` and `B` where each depends on the other, and each entry/onLoad emits a side effect if executed. Run loader. Assert: cycle error is reported with both plugin names, neither plugin entry side effect occurs, and neither `onLoad` runs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A plugin's `onLoad` hook is only invoked after the plugin's entry module has been imported and executed.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is about runtime sequencing between module import side effects and hook invocation within the loader. Mocking imports can hide real ordering mistakes.","test_description":"Create one plugin whose entry module sets `globalThis.pluginInitFlag = true` at top level and exports `onLoad` that records the flag value it observes. Run loader. Assert `onLoad` was called and observed `pluginInitFlag === true`, proving import execution happened first.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.86,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When a plugin throws an error during its `onLoad` hook, the loader continues initializing the remaining plugins that do not depend on it.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Need real orchestration across dependency graph + error isolation semantics. Unit tests on error handler alone can miss incorrect stop-the-world behavior in loader flow.","test_description":"Create plugins: `A` throws in `onLoad`; `B` depends on `A`; `C` independent. Run loader. Assert: error for `A` is reported, `B` is skipped/not initialized due to dependency, and `C` still initializes successfully (`onLoad` called).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.12,"Integration":0.82,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
